# Class Monitoring implementation plan

## Goal
Implement a "Class Status" (Κατάσταση Τάξης) feature that allows the teacher to view low-fps thumbnails of all student screens in a grid. This involves:
- Adding a button in the teacher toolbox using `monitoring.svg`
- Adding a Monitoring section underneath Settings -> Screen Sharing
- Requesting an IPC screen capture from the Student's Electron app or falling back to WebRTC tab capture if in browser
- Sending the scaled-down JPEG frame over Socket.IO to the Server, which broadcasts it to the Teacher
- Implementing a scrollable modal pop-up for the "Class Status" grid (similar to Media Library)
- Adding settings (Top-level toggle to enable/disable. When enabled, reveals a dropdown for refresh interval: 5s, 8s, 15s, 20s, auto)
- Displaying a system notification to students when monitoring is active

## Proposed Changes

### 1. IPC & Screen Capture in Electron
#### [MODIFY] server/electron-main.js
- Add `ipcMain.handle('capture-screen', ...)` using `desktopCapturer` to capture the primary screen and compress it to JPEG.
- Inject a `preload.js` (or expose `window.electron`) to allow [client/main.js](file:///c:/Users/Teo/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/ClassSend/client/main.js) to call `capture-screen`. (If nodeIntegration is already enabled, we can use `require('electron')` directly).

### 2. UI Additions (Teacher Side)
#### [MODIFY] client/index.html
- Add `<button id="btn-tool-class-status">` in the Teacher Tools menu (`teacher-tools-section`) using `monitoring.svg`.
- Add a Modals/Screens for the "Class Status" grid (`class-status-modal`). Make it a modal pop-up with a scrollable container. Title uses `monitoring.svg`.
- Add a new section in Settings -> Screen Sharing underneath the existing settings for Monitoring. It will have a main toggle. The dropdown for intervals will only be visible when the toggle is enabled.

### 3. Localization (Translations)
#### [MODIFY] client/translations.js
- Add English and Greek strings for:
  - "btn-tool-class-status" -> "Class Status" / "Κατάσταση Τάξης"
  - "monitoring-header" -> "Monitoring" / "Παρακολούθηση"
  - "monitoring-warning" -> "Warning: This feature may burden the network/computers" / "Προειδοποίηση: Μπορεί να επιβαρύνει το δίκτυο ή/και τους υπολογιστές"
  - "student-monitoring-notice" -> "You are being monitored by the teacher." / "Παρακολουθείστε από τον δάσκαλο."

### 4. Client Logic
#### [MODIFY] client/main.js
- **Teacher:**
  - Logic to open the Class Status modal and iterate over connected users to show thumbnail boxes.
  - Emit `socket.emit('start-monitoring', { interval })` when enabled, and `stop-monitoring` when disabled.
  - Listen for `socket.on('monitoring-frame', (data) => ...)` to update the `src` of the Image in the grid.
  - Handle Fullscreen click to emit `socket.emit('request-high-res-frame', { targetUserId })`.
  - UI logic for the settings toggle to show/hide the interval dropdown.
- **Student:**
  - Listen for `socket.on('start-monitoring')` to trigger a system toast notification: "You are being monitored".
  - Start an interval to capture the screen (via `ipcRenderer.invoke('capture-screen', { quality: 'low' })` or Canvas) and `socket.emit('monitoring-frame', ...)`
  - Listen for `socket.on('request-high-res-frame')` to instantly capture and send a high-quality JPEG.
  - Ensure any interval is cleared when `stop-monitoring` is received or settings change. Images should only be kept in RAM.

### 5. Server Relaying
#### [MODIFY] server/index.js
- Forward `start-monitoring`, `stop-monitoring`, `request-high-res-frame`, and `monitoring-frame` socket events between Teacher and Students in the same `classId`.

## Verification Plan
1. **Manual Verification:**
   - Launch the Server / Teacher instance.
   - Launch 1 or more Student instances.
   - Teacher toggles Monitoring ON in Settings (verifying dropdown appears).
   - Teacher clicks on "Class Status" tool, opens the scrollable modal.
   - Verify that the Student instances flash a notification "You are being monitored".
   - Verify that thumbnails of the Student screens appear on the Teacher's grid updating every X seconds.
   - Test the Fullscreen button on a thumbnail to ensure a high-quality frame is instantly requested and displayed.
   - Verify that disabling the feature stops all intervals and completely hides the tool, ensuring zero network/CPU load when disabled.
